<exercise id="fs-id1165810943619" print-placement="end">
<problem id="fs-id1165811069146">
<para id="id182133">Margaret considers five purchases in the amounts 5, 17, 21, 8, 15 dollars
with respective probabilities 0.37, 0.22, 0.38, 0.81, 0.63. Anne contemplates six
purchases in the amounts 8, 15, 12, 18, 15, 12 dollars, with respective probabilities
0.77, 0.52, 0.23, 0.41, 0.83, 0.58. Assume that all eleven possible purchases form an
independent class.</para>
    <!--empty paragraphs get left behind.-->
    <list id="id182143" display="block" list-type="enumerated" number-style="lower-alpha"><item id="uid9">Determine the distribution for <emphasis effect="italics">X</emphasis>, the amount purchased by Margaret.

</item>
      <item id="uid10">Determine the distribution for <emphasis effect="italics">Y</emphasis>, the amount purchased by Anne.

</item>
      <item id="uid11">Determine the distribution for <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mi>Z</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>X</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mi>Y</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math>, the total amount the two purchase.

</item>
    </list>
    <para id="id182241"><emphasis effect="italics">Suggestion</emphasis> for part (c). Let MATLAB perform the calculations.</para>
    <!--empty paragraphs get left behind.-->
    <code id="id182253" display="block">[r,s] = ndgrid(X,Y);
[t,u] = ndgrid(PX,PY);
z = r + s;
pz = t.*u;
[Z,PZ] = csort(z,pz);
</code>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-id8626612">
 
    <!--empty paragraphs get left behind.-->
    <code id="id249582" display="block">% file <link window="new" document="m24179" target-id="cid34">npr06_18.m</link>
cx = [5 17 21 8 15 0];
cy = [8 15 12 18 15 12 0];
pmx = minprob(0.01*[37 22 38 81 63]);
pmy = minprob(0.01*[77 52 23 41 83 58]);
<link window="new" document="m24179" target-id="cid34">npr06_18</link>
[X,PX] = canonicf(cx,pmx);  [Y,PY] = canonicf(cy,pmy);
[r,s] = ndgrid(X,Y);   [t,u] = ndgrid(PX,PY);
z = r + s;   pz = t.*u;
[Z,PZ] = csort(z,pz);
a = length(Z)
a  =  125              % 125 different values
plot(Z,cumsum(PZ))  % See figure     Plotting details omitted
</code>
</solution>
